entries.title: WHO Welcomes China's Accounting of 60,000 Covid Deaths
entries.description: Previously Beijing had logged daily Covid deaths in single digits since the start of December.

entries.title: Russian Strikes Sap Ukraine Mobile Network of Vital Power
entries.description: Telecom operators and internet providers are scouring suppliers for better batteries and generators.

entries.title: Ukraine Searches for Survivors After Apartment-Block Strike
entries.description: At least 21 died after a Russian missile struck an apartment building, one of the worst attacks on civilian areas since the start of Moscow’s full-scale invasion. The death toll deepened the sense of urgency among allies to provide Ukraine more sophisticated weapons.

entries.title: Iraqi Prime Minister Supports Indefinite U.S. Troop Presence
entries.description: In an interview, Mohammed al-Sudani signaled a less confrontational posture toward Washington early in his term than his Iran-backed political allies have taken.

entries.title: Iran Limits Supply of Cheap Oil to Syria, Leaving Ally in Crisis
entries.description: Iran has doubled the price it charges Syria for crude oil, touching off a fuel shortage for its ally as its own economy sputters.

entries.title: Nepal Plane Crash Kills Dozens, Some Remain Missing
entries.description: A Yeti Airlines plane carrying 72 people crashed into a river gorge in central Nepal, killing at least 62.
